div.ab:
24. Just as in coats of arms, clear, glowing Gold 

can indicate nobility and majesty,

Silver, purity and merciful justice; 

Red meaning magnificence, courage and valor;

Blue, faithfulness, and the practice of knowledge;

Green, beauty, goodness and joy; and to continue,

Purple, abundance, the favor of Gods and Men;

Black, humility and the sadness dwelling in the heart.

28. A child up to seven years old after birth

is Silver or white, innocent and charming;

Blue is an inexperienced Youth up to fifteen years;

Gold-yellow, the Young man up to twenty years;

Green is a Young man up to thirty.

Red, a valiant Man up to fifty;

Purple is to an elder up to seventy;

Black, in mourning, is reserved for death.
